                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mihr va-Mushtarī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">مهر و مشتری</title>
                     <note>F1a: impressions of seals of Ibrahim Qutbshah, Muhammad Quli Qutbshah, Muhammad Qutbshah, dated 1021? (1612-13?), Sultan Muhammad dated 1117? (1705-6?), Hajji Rajab 'Ali, dated 1187 (1773-4), Ibrahim, dated 1213 (1798-9). Folio preceding text, recto, in pencil: Đ3.3.0 Verso: a) Purchased by the Oriental Translation Committee b) Two impressions of the seal of Sultan Muhammad noted above. Written diagonally in the margins of ff6-23 is a section of a mathnawi telling of the love of Mahmud and Ayaz, so far unidentified. Ruled margins and dividing panels. Headings in red. Illuminated panel over beginning of text. Rather crude later dividing panels on ff6-16, some with painted flowers.</note>
                     <incipit>Bi-nam-i padishah-i 'alam-i 'ishq</incipit>
